<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: What classes are good for PvP?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Zariin">Zariin</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:48 a.m. 12/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: What classes are good for PvP?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=803" TARGET=_self>What classes are good for PvP?</A> (Vlar)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I think these early reports are a bit hasty. There will be different level stratification in which certain classes will be "The Best" or "In the Top Three."

<P>Necro's are "good" right now at low level because of one direct damage spell that is hard to resist by other low level characters. Monks are better than average at early levels due to thier natural armor class and hand to hand skills--no need to worry about purchasing/acquiring another rusty weapon or cloth armor set right after death...they can just wade back into the fray.
<P>Another set of "The Best PvP Classes" will emerge every so often as people gain a few levels.
<P>For Example: The first people to get SOTW will be veritable Gods for a while....
<BR>Guerilla hit-and-runs at their finest.....
<P>Zariin
<P><i>This might be a little premature but I want to get a thread going about which classes are too powerful and which ones need a little work. So far I have seen that necromancers and monks seem to be a really good choice for PvP. So lets try to get some input and find out if there will be a power class....I don't want everyone to only be a wizard because he is the strongest. Also ideas on what could make a class more viable for PvP.
<P>Guide Vlar</i>
<P>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
